{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"Included with: <b> ἔσχᾰτος</b>, η, ον, <br /> also ος, ον [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-3rd c.BC: Aratus Epicus 625 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>](probably from ἐκ, ἐξ, perhaps eĝhzκατος (compare ἐχθός) like{ἔγ-κατα}): <br /><Level2><b>__I</b></Level2> of Space, as always in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Homerus Epicus \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>], <b>farthest, uttermost, extreme,</b> θάλαμος ἔ. the <b>hindmost</b> chamber, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 21.9; ἔσχατοι ἄλλων \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]<b>at the end of the lines,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 10.434, compare 8.225 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; ἔσχατοι ἀνδρῶν, of the Aethiopians, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 1.23; οἰκέομεν..ἔσχατοι 6.205; ἐσχάτη τῶν οἰκεομένων ἡ Ἰνδική 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 3.106, compare 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 2.96, etc.; τὸ ἔ. τῆς ἀγορᾶς 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Historia Graeca (Hellenica)” 3.3.5; ὑπ᾽..ἐσχάτην στήλην 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Electra” 720 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; τάξις ἐ. the <b>farthest part of</b> the army, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “Aj.” 4: _plural_, ἔσχατα γαίης 8th-7th c.BC: Hesiodus Epicus “Theogonia” 731; τὰ ἔ. τῶν στρατοπέδων 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 4.96; ἐπ᾽ ἔσχατα χθονός 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Fragmenta” 956; αἱ ἐπ᾽ ἔσχατα τοῦ ἄστεως οἰκίαι 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 8.95 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; ἐξ ἐσχάτων ἐς ἔσχατα ἀπικέσθαι from <b>end</b> to <b>end,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 7.100, compare 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “de Vectigalibus” 1.6; παρ᾽ ἔσχατα λίμνης 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Phaedo” 113b, compare 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 3.106 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]:—in various senses, <b>uppermost,</b> ἐ. πυρά [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Electra” 900 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; <b>lowest, deepest,</b> ἀΐδας [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 3rd c.BC: Theocritus Poeta Bucolicus 16.52; ἅλς “Anthologia Graeca” 13.27 (3rd c.BC: Phalaecus Epigrammaticus) \">Refs 3rd c.BC+</a>]; <b>innermost,</b> σάρκες [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Trachiniae” 1053 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; <b>last, hindmost,</b> ἤλαυνε δ᾽ ἔ. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “El.” 734 \">Refs</a>]; ἐπ᾽ ἐσχάτῳ at the <b>close</b> of a document, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “PTeb.” 68.54 (2nd c.BC), etc. \">Refs 2nd c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__I.2</b></Level3> of Degree, <b>uttermost, highest,</b> τὸ ἔ. κορυφοῦται βασιλεῦσι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “O.” 1.113; ἀνορέαι ἔ. [prev. author] “I.” 4(3).11; σοφία 4th c.AD: Libanius Sophista “Orationes” 59.88 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; of misfortunes, sufferings, etc., <b>utmost, last, worst,</b> πόνος, ἀδικία, κίνδυνοι, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Phaedrus” 247b, “R.” 361a, “Grg.” 511d; ὀδύναι αἱ ἔ. [prev. author] “Prt.” 354b \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; δῆμος ἔ. <b>extreme</b> democracy, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Politica” 1296a2. \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level4><b>__I.2.b</b></Level4> <i>substantive</i>, τὸ ἔ., τὰ ἔ., <b>the utmost,</b> ἐς τὸ ἔ. κακοῦ ἀπιγμένοι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 8.52; τετρῦσθαι ἐς τὸ ἔ. κακοῦ [prev. author] 1.22; without _Article_, ἐπ᾽ ἔσχατα βαίνεις 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Oedipus Coloneus” 217 (Lyric poetry); προβᾶσ᾽ ἐπ᾽ ἔσχατον θράσους [prev. author] “Ant.” 853 (Lyric poetry); ἐπ᾽ ἔ. ἐλθεῖν ἀηδίας 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Phaedrus” 240d, compare “R.” 361d, etc.; ὃ πάντων κακῶν ἔσχατόν ἐστι, τοῦτο πάσχει [prev. author] “Phd.” 83c; οἱ τὰ ἔ. πεποιηκότες 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Institutio Cyri (Cyropaedia)” 8.8.2 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ζημιοῦσθαι πᾶσι τοῖς ἐ., Latin <i>extremis suppliciis,</i> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Politicus” 297e \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἔσχατ᾽ ἐσχάτων κακά <b>worst of possible</b> evils, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Philoctetes” 65, compare 4th-3rd c.BC: Philemo Comicus 178; εἰς τὰ ἔ. ἐληλυθώς “UPZ” 60.12 (2nd c.BC)\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: <i>comparative</i> οὔτε γὰρ τοῦ ἐσχάτου -ώτερον εἴη ἄν τι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Metaphysica” 1055a20: _superlative_ -ώτατος\">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>] <i>falsa lectio</i> in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Historia Graeca (Hellenica)” 2.3.49, compare 2nd c.AD: Phrynichus Atticista 51; τὰ -ώτατα 1st c.BC: Philodemus Philosophus “περὶ τοῦ καθ᾽ Ὅμηρον ἀγαθοῦ βασιλέως” p.320. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__I.3</b></Level3> of Persons, <b>lowest, meanest,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st c.BC: Diodorus Siculus Historicus 8.18, 2nd-3rd c.AD: Dio Cassius Historicus 42.5, 4th c.AD: Alciphro Epistolographus 3.43: proverbial, οὐδείς, οὐδ᾽ ὁ Μυσῶν ἔ.,\">Refs 1st c.BC+</a>] i.e. <b>the meanest</b> of mankind,[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" Magnes 5, compare 4th-3rd c.BC: Philemo Comicus 77; in 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Theaetetus” 209b \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] it seems to mean the <b>remotest</b> of mankind, compare πρὸς ἐσχάτην Μυσῶν variant in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “App.Prov.” 2.85 (παρὰ τοῖς ἐ. τῆς Μυσίας 15th c.AD: Apostolius Paroemiographus 8.1); similarly οὐδὲ τὸν ἔσχατον Καρῶν 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus 2.871b. \">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__I.4</b></Level3> of Time, <b>last,</b> ἐς τὸ ἔ. to the <b>end,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 7.107, 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 3.46 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἔ. πλόος, ναυτιλίαι, <b>the end of</b> it, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “P.” 10.28, “N.” 3.22 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἐσχάτας ὑπὲρ ῥίζας over <b>the last</b> scion of the race, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Antigone” 599 (Lyric poetry)\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἔ. Ἑλλήνων, Ῥωμαίων, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus “Philopoemen” 1, “Brut.” 44: _neuter_ ἔσχατον,\">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>] as <i>adverb</i>, <b>for the last time,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Oedipus Coloneus” 1550 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; <b>finally, best of all,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" NT.1Cor.15.8 \">NT</a>]; <b>at the latest,</b> ἔ. ἐν τρισὶ μησίν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “SIG” 1219.11 (Gambreion, 3rd c.BC),compare “Inscription Prien.” 4.45 (4th c.BC)\">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; εἰς τὴν ἐσχάτην at the <b>last,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" LXX.Eccl.1.11 \">LXX</a>]; ἐπ᾽ ἐσχάτῳ[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"LXX.2Ki.24.25, +others: \">LXX</a>] <i>substantive</i> ἐσχάτη, ἡ, <b>end,</b> οὐχ ἕξεις ἐ. καλήν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Astrampsychus Onirocriticus “Oracula” 21.4, compare 40.3. \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__I.5</b></Level3> in the Logic of [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus, τὰ ἔ.\">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>] are the <b>last</b> or <i>lowest species, </i>[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “Metaphorical” 1059b26, or \">Refs</a>]<b>individuals,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"[prev. work]998b16,compare “Anthologia Graeca” 0.96b12, +others; τὸ ἔ. ἄτομον “Metaphorical” 1058b10. \">Refs</a>]<br /><Level4><b>__I.5.b</b></Level4> ὁ ἔ. ὅρος the <b>minor</b> term of a syllogism, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “EN” 1147b14. \">Refs</a>]<br /><Level4><b>__I.5.c</b></Level4> <b>last step</b> in <i>geometrical</i> analysis or <b>ultimate condition</b> of action, τὸ ἔ. ἀρχὴ τῆς πράξεως [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “de An.” 433a16. \">Refs</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <i>adverb</i> -τως <b>to the uttermost, exceedingly,</b> πῦρ ἐ. καίει [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Hippocrates Medicus “περὶ τέχνης” 8; ἐ. διαμάχεσθαι 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Historia Animalium” 613a11; ἐ. φιλοπόλεμος 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Anabasis” 2.6.1; φοβοῦμαί σ᾽ ἐ. 4th-3rd c.BC: Menander Comicus 912, compare 4th-3rd c.BC: Epicurus Philosophus “Epistulae” 1p.31U. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level4><b>__II.b</b></Level4> -τως διακεῖσθαι to be <b>at the last extremity,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.BC: Polybius Historicus 1.24.2, 1st c.BC: Diodorus Siculus Historicus 18.48; ἔχειν NT.Mark.5.23; ἀπορεῖν 1st c.BC: Philodemus Philosophus “περὶ οἰκονομίας” p.72J. \">NT+2nd c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.2</b></Level3> so ἐς τὸ ἔ.,=ἐσχάτως, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 7.229; εἰς τὰ ἔ. 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Historia Graeca (Hellenica)” 5.4.33; εἰς τὰ ἔ. μάλα [prev. author] “Lac.” 1.2; τὸ ἔ. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<b>finally, in the end,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Gorgias” 473c \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; but, τὸ ἔ. <b>what is worst of all,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"[prev. work] 508d. \">Refs</a>]","strongNumber":"G2079","accentedUnicode":"ἐσχάτως","relatedNos":[{"strongNumber":"G2078","matchingForm":"ἔσχατος","stepTransliteration":"eschatos","gloss":"last/least","_zh_tw_Gloss":"末後, 末, 在後","_es_Gloss":"último/menor","_zh_Gloss":"末后, 末, 在后"}],"shortDef":"- finally, i.e. (with G2192) at the extremity of life","mediumDef":"- finally, i.e. (with G2192) at the extremity of life","stepGloss":"extremely","ste